approach to abortion law in Ireland. Directly challenging grounds-based abortion law, this accessible guide brings together feminist analysis, comparative research, human rights law, and political awareness to propose a new constitutional and legislative settlement on reproductive autonomy in Ireland. It offers practical proposals for policymakers and advocates, including model legislation, making it an essential campaigning tool leading up to the referendum.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAbortionxLaw and legislationzIreland. 0aAbortion. 0aConstitutional lawzIreland. 0aConstitutional law. 0aReferendumzIreland. 0aReferendum. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Abortion & Birth Control.2bisacsh1 aEnright, Máiréad, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831111966640 cprintz978144734751440uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447347545?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447347545zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447347545/original  a978-3-11-119666-4 Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA